<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Glane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Is Reinforce leather worth the trouble?  What kind of armor rating does it have?  I have a blacksmith friend that can make the boning for me, and my skill is 27 (one successfull backpack). There is just so many HQ pelts in W. Karana, I hate to let them just sit there. What kind of chance am I looking at?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Shenendoah Skywolf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I have tailoring and blacksmithing skills of about 29 or 30.  I can make steel bonings fairly easily but after 50pp and 15 consecutive failures I decided its not worth the time and money to make re-inforced.  I can buy or aquire items of equal or greater ac value for less money and these items often have stat modifiers attributed to them.  It is sad that this is the case but making studded to increase your skill is even more time consuming and useless because studded has the same ac as leather so impossible to sell for a profit.  Besides have you ever tried to make metal flakes...BORING!!!  I have never seen re-inforced auctioned on my server (bristlebane) so it appears that others have reached this conclusion as well.  Good Luck!  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ericcrown</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Yes studded armor is better to sell to the store then to sell to people. But I find if you get a couple of lower level druids and monks to help get the pelts you can pay them with the studded armor. Studded armor is the same ac as leather but most of it is 1 ac higher than rawhide. So find yourself a couple of level 6 to 12 monks and druids and make them a quest. Tell them to bring back medium quality pelts in exchange for studded armor. Remind them that its a hit or miss skill so they dont get mad you didnt make anything. Most find that they gain exp in finding them and dont mind too much. I usually offer 25 plat for 2 backpacks of medium quality pelts. Everyone loves that quest hehe. I got 3 regulars that contact me constantly with more pelts. Its not about making money. You want to make quick money goto najena and kill her. Then sell her flowing black robe for 200 plat. Or sell her silver tome for 350. In any case trade skills are not for just the individual. Its for all. So when I do tailoring, I'm thinking about all the newbies who need armor to make it to level 5 or i think about all those druids and monks left without something nice to wear. Good luck in the skill. It is the hardest traid skill out there.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">elvish123</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Who is Najena and where can I find her? I have only L3-5 characters on Quillous server and need money badly. How does she con and can I take her with 4th and 5th level guys?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">BrianBori</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">hehehe.. not the right message board for this... but NO... u cannot take her out at that lvl... u won't even make it NEAR her... hehe.. keep playin... u got MANY lvl's ahead of u..</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Maven</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Firstly Tailoring isn't worth it.  I have made some small pieces of reinforced and studded items and actually there very cool, especially for the medium races<BR>EG. Reinforced gorget WT:  .5 <BR>    Banded Gorget     WT: 2.0<BR> the difference after bonus is only 1<BR>I don't believe the difference is quite that good on later items but still it can be great for weaker rogues and some other classes.<P>Tailoring is extremely difficult... there is hours of smithing with no increases because your allready maxed for the simple thing your doing that fails still quite often.  It's very expensive and HQ and MQ pelts while easier to get since the last major patch are still fairly hard to get.  I think IQ should play a part in how fast you get increases, i have a 98 int but still can fail 10-15 times in a row and not get a single increase either.  On the other hand sometimes you get 2 in a row also...so...<BR>My tailoring still is very low at 33... but I really would like to keep trying some more as I get more pelts...Mainly because I seem to be one of the better tailors around... yes i know there are some better... but i have never seen anyone sell anything other then the 10-slot backpacks.<P>That's the other thing about the stupid skills you have to get hard to get items from creatures who rarely drop them... that's why make poison is a screw over for rogues at such a high level... who wants to go hunt crap that doesn't even give any exp at all...'<P>If anyone has any questions... i will try to visit this page again some time this month<P>Maven<BR>vmaven@aol.com<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
